{*
  BOOE base layout. The one canonical shell for every page (Home + all narrative
  pages + route stubs). It also BOOTSTRAPS the shared data collections.

  Per-page vars: child templates set these at the very top, before {block content}.
  Child top-level {var}s reach the layout (that is how the head gets its title):
    {var $pageTitle = 'The Trinity'}        page name (omit on Home)
    {var $pageDescription = '...'}          meta description (optional)
    {var $pageSlug = 'trinity'}             URL slug, drives canonical (omit on Home)
    {var $pageCss = 'trinity'}              links /assets/css/pages/trinity.css (optional)
    {var $bodyClass = 'page-inner'}         extra <body> class (optional)

  SHARED DATA ($relics, $acts): Latte {include} does NOT export variables and a
  child's own top-level {var} is NOT visible inside its {block content}. BUT a
  layout-level {var} IS visible in every child block. So the two data collections
  are defined here, once, and are automatically available in EVERY page's
  {block content} with zero setup. To edit a relic or an Act, edit the array here.
*}

